OL,5, The number of hate crimes recorded by  
OL,6, police in England and Wales has risen  
OL,7, by 26% - to 155,841 in the year to     
OL,8, March 2022, Home Office figures show.  
OL,10,FMore than two-thirds - 109,843 - were  
OL,11,Fracist hate crimes.                    
OL,13,FBut crimes against transgender people  
OL,14,Fsaw the biggest rise, with 4,355       
OL,15,Freports, up 56% from the previous year.
OL,17,FThe Home Office said the overall rise  
OL,18,Fcould be due to better recording by    
OL,19,Fpolice - and fewer had been recorded   
OL,20,Funder Covid restrictions in 2020-21.   
